.TH "pm_clk_add_notifier" 9 "pm_clk_add_notifier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_clk_add_notifier \- Add bus type notifier for power management clocks.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pm_clk_add_notifier
.BI "(struct bus_type *bus "  ","
.BI "struct pm_clk_notifier_block *clknb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
Bus type to add the notifier to.
.IP "clknb" 12
Notifier to be added to the given bus type.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The nb member of \fIclknb\fP is not expected to be initialized and its
notifier_call member will be replaced with \fBpm_clk_notify\fP.  However,
the remaining members of \fIclknb\fP should be populated prior to calling this
routine.
